to the editor re companies trim health benefits for many retirees as costs surge front page may 10 the health care industry is not interested in health it is interested in disease it is mystifying that americans can not grasp this fact or take the responsibility for their own health instead we pay the industry to manage the consequences of our poor diets and lifestyle habits when we wake up to the facts we will be able to do something about the paralyzing costs of health care hope alexander griscom phillips me may 10 2002

